						<summary>

						<p>This is dated in the 8th year of Parakēsarivarman who has been surmised to be <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi> This is an incomplete <hi rend="bold">abstract of certain inscriptions</hi> recapitulating the endowments in land for worship, offerings and lamps in the temple, made by several persons in the 18th and 20th years of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I</hi>, which was orderd to be re-engraved out of their worn-out originals cut on the step of the old central shrine of the temple, by the assembly of Uttamaśīli-chaturvēdimaṅgalam. </p>						

						</summary>
